1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 192 of Title 10, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 There is hereby created the Oklahoma Youth Advisory Council to
5 serve as a dynamic platform for young people to examine, evaluate,
6 and discuss the issues, interests, and needs that impact Oklahoma
7 youth both now and in the future. The Council shall formally advise
8 and make actionable recommendations to elected officials on these
9 matters, ensuring that the voices of Oklahoma's youth are
10 meaningfully incorporated into public policy. The issues may
11 include, but need not be limited to, education, employment, and
12 economic opportunity, access to state and local government services,
13 the environment, behavioral and physical health, safe environments
14 for youth, substance abuse, poverty, and increased youth
15 participation in state and local government.
16 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 193 of Title 10, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Council shall consist of fifty-three (53) members as
20 follows:
21 1. Forty-eight members representing each of the Oklahoma Senate
22 districts; and
23 2. Five at-large members representing the federally recognized
24 Indian tribal governments within the State of Oklahoma.
