1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 194 of Title 10, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Oklahoma Youth Advisory Council shall have the following
5 duties and responsibilities:
6 1. Adopt written bylaws setting forth a leadership structure
7 for the Council, which may be amended if necessary;
8 2. Work with any existing and appropriate local and state youth
9 groups to identify the concerns and needs of youth in Oklahoma;
10 3. Advise and make oral and written recommendations to members
11 of the Oklahoma Legislature on proposed or pending legislation;
12 4. Work with any existing and appropriate local and state youth
13 groups to collect, analyze, and provide information on issues
14 related to youth to the legislative committees, commissions, task
15 forces, and state agencies and departments as appropriate;
16 5. Consult with any existing local-level youth advisory
17 Councils for input and potential solutions on issues related to
18 youth; and
19 6. Set priorities and establish any committees that may be
20 necessary to achieve the goals of the Council.
21 B. 1. At the first meeting, the Council shall determine the
22 location and time of future meetings, as well as any other
23 procedural issues it deems necessary.
24
