1 2. The Council shall meet at least four times each year, with
2 two meetings occurring during the regular legislative session and
3 two meetings occurring after the regular legislative session has
4 concluded. Council members may attend and participate in Council
5 meetings remotely, but at least two of the Council's meetings each
6 year shall be held in person with all attending members at the same
7 physical location. Additional meetings may be held at the
8 discretion of Council leadership, subject to available funds.
9 3. All meetings of the Council shall be open to the public.
10 4. The Council has the authority to develop rules and
11 procedures to govern its activities.
12 C. The Council shall utilize news outlets and publications,
13 public awareness campaigns, and a website to develop and maintain
14 regular communication concerning its activities with the youth of
15 Oklahoma, the State of Oklahoma, and interested parties.
