2 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
3 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 196 of Title 10, unless there is
4 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
5 A. The Oklahoma Youth Advisory Council Review Committee is
6 hereby created to review the work of the Oklahoma Youth Advisory
7 Council and to recommend legislation affecting Oklahoma youth.
8 B. The Review Committee shall be comprised of the legislative
9 members of the Council, five nonlegislative Council members who are
10 appointed by the Council, and one legislative member appointed by
11 the legislative members of the Council.
12 1. The five legislative members of the Review Committee shall
13 serve as voting members. All other members are nonvoting members.
14 2. In odd-numbered years, the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of
15 Representatives shall appoint the chair of the Review Committee and
16 the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate shall appoint
17 the vice-chair. In even-numbered years, the President Pro-Tempore
18 of the Oklahoma State Senate shall appoint the chair and the Speaker
19 of the Oklahoma House of Representatives shall appoint the vice-
20 chair.
21 C. The Review Committee may meet up to three times each interim
22 and recommend up to six bills to the legislative Council based on
23 the Council's recommendations and findings.
